 



xTV Announces Microsoft Windows®-powered HDMI Device for the Enterprise | Business Wire


























































xTV Announces Microsoft Windows®-powered HDMI 
      Device for the Enterprise






      “xTVNow” HDMI Device Powers The Next Generation Enterprise TV Networks
    









Download



Windows Media Video


Quicktime


MPEG-4 Video






Loading media player...




xTV Launches xTVNow for the enterprise


???pagination.previous???
???pagination.next???







xTV Launches xTVNow for the enterprise





Windows Media Video




Quicktime




MPEG-4 Video














Full Size








Small








Preview








Thumbnail














March 11, 2015 09:30 AM Eastern Daylight Time



REDWOOD SHORES, Calif.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--xTV, 
      (ASX:XTV), the next generation media network, today announced a 
      cloud-based online TV network device to enable any screen to become 
      cloud-TV enabled. The product, xTVNow is a fully self-contained HDMI 
      device that is powered by the xTV online TV platform, Microsoft 
      Windows®, and Microsoft Azure®.
    


      xTV offers a real-time platform for companies looking to integrate their 
      social needs which are then custom built and loaded up to the xTVNow 
      device to create a company’s own Online .TV. xTVNow plugs into the HDMI 
      port on most smart televisions and is no bigger than a USB storage 
      device. Companies then have access to a real-time feed, which is updated 
      with tailored selections from YouTubeTM, TwitterTM, 
      news services, and the company’s own media content.
    

      “90% of the enterprise screens in the market are idle,” said Joe Ward, 
      CEO of xTV. “Every retail, hospitality and healthcare business globally 
      can now light up these screens with their own, real-time, interactive 
      screens.”
    

      Unlike other devices in the marketplace which require a PC or laptop to 
      transmit to the device, xTVNow is fully self-contained. Once content is 
      on the screens, users can download information including marketing and 
      product information through QR codes on their phones and tablets. With 
      xTVNow companies can simply plug in the device and have a personalized 
      interactive experience across several devices. xTVNow is a new way for 
      enterprise companies to monetize their digital screens.
    

      “The Internet Of Things (IOT) plays an important role in the future 
      landscape of the Microsoft eco-system,” said Gustavo Semencato, Senior 
      Product Manager, Internet Of Things at Microsoft. “We’re excited about 
      the possibilities these real-time, interactive screens can bring to the 
      enterprise from xTV’s collaboration with Azure.”
    

About xTV Networks, Ltd.


      xTV is the Next Generation Media Company, which delivers the platform to 
      build your .TV.
    

      Founded in 2011, the company’s vision is to deliver any organization 
      with the capability to lower the cost of content production and multiply 
      the consumption of their media by delivering a true, real‐time, 
      lean‐back TV experience, without the need to install new devices or 
      applications. xTV is based in Redwood City, California.
    

      For more information, please visit www.xtv.net.
    




Contacts

      xTV Networks, Ltd.Joe Ward, CEOjoe.ward@xtv.netorAlissa 
      Guler, VP Marketingalissa.guler@xtv.netorMedia 
      Inquiries:GutenbergCommunicationsMeagan Ostrowski, 
      212-810-4394Meagan@Gutenbergpr.com





















