Message :
*Required fields





9851a390-7804-4984-9944-8a77d637c8a0.pdf
    




      19 April 2016
    



      Australian Securities Exchange 20 Bridge Street
    

      SYDNEY NSW 2000
    



      Via Electronic Lodgement
    



      EXCLUSIVE OPTION AGREEMENT TO ACQUIRE 3D VIDEO TECHNOLOGY COMPANY
    



      Highlights:
    




          Exclusive option agreement to acquire certain assets from Buffalo Pacific LLC, a Florida limited liability company (Buffalo) together with the shares of Telepresence Technology, LLC, a limited liability company incorporated in Texas (TPT);
        





          TPT has developed innovative and patented 3D imaging technology;
        





          Proposed ownership interest of 100% in TPT subject to exercise of the Option and subsequent completion of the underlying definitive agreements; and
        





          New 3DCLOUDTV first demonstrated at AT&T's Technology Leadership Conference in Singapore, April 14 2016; with overwhelmingly positive feedback, resulting in a Technology Roadshow over the next six weeks in Australia and Singapore through xTV Networks Channel Sponsor AT&T
        





          BACKGROUND
        



          The Board of xTV Networks Limited (ACN 124 251 396) (ASX: XTV) (xTV or the Company) is pleased to announce it has entered into a binding terms sheet (Terms Sheet) pursuant to which it has an exclusive option to acquire technology assets from Buffalo and 100% of the issued share capital of TPT (the Business) (Option), subject to satisfaction of conditions precedent (Proposed Acquisition).
        



          xTV's Option to acquire the Business pursuant to the Proposed Acquisition may be exercised at xTV's election at any time up until May 31, 2016.
        





          BUFFALO AND TPT BUSINESS
        



          Buffalo is a marketing entity with rights to market the technology from TPT. Buffalo is seeking to become an end customer of the newly combined 3DCLOUDTV product.
        



          The assets held by Buffalo and TPT are information technology products which produce 3D images. The intellectual property interests of TPT include nine patents granted in the USA and one in Europe.
        



          xTV intends to restructure the assets of Buffalo and TPT to integrate them into the xTV Cloud TV Network platform by using their 3D imaging technologies as an additional access point for xTV's content, providing a unique 3D TV experience. The Proposed Acquisition will therefore add another access point for the xTV Cloud TV Network operated by xTV, being 3DCLOUDTV (Products).
        



          The xTV Cloud TV Network platform will be available as a 3DCLOUDTV service in the same form as other access points and, additionally, the acquisition of the Business will bring the following benefits:
        




              introduction of a superior video on-demand playback experience;
            





              reducing the dependence on the touch screen kiosk interface by using the xTV Cloud TV Network and introduction of the mobile first interactive experience; and
            





              use of the 3DCLOUDTV experience to attract customers to the xTV Cloud TV- customer network.
            



              xTV will continue to operate its xTV Cloud TV Network with a focus on the development of 3D Cloud TV as an access point.
            



              As the technology industry continues to develop, xTV will continue to add any necessary access points for the xTV Cloud TV Network to ensure it remains attractive to xTV's consumers.
            





          KEY ACQUISITION TERMS
        



          On exercise of the Option, pursuant to the Terms Sheet xTV has agreed to acquire the Business subject to the satisfaction or waiver of conditions precedent. The shareholders of Buffalo and TPT are not associated with the board of directors of xTV.
        



          A summary of the key terms of the Proposed Acquisition is set out below.
        





                Initial Consideration and Deferred Consideration
              



                On exercise of the Option, and subject to satisfaction or waiver of conditions precedent to the Proposed Acquisition, in consideration for acquiring the Business xTV has agreed to an initial consideration comprising:
              




                    xTV will receive an initial non-exclusive license and resale agreement relating to all Products and technologies of Buffalo and TPT in order to cover near term sales activities until such time as the acquisition as defined in paragraph (b) below,
                  





                    upon payments by xTV to BP and TPT totalling USD$13.5 million, the acquisition of the Business will be triggered, and
                  





                    upon the acquisition of the Business, 30,000,000 fully paid ordinary shares in the capital of xTV (the "Shares") will be issued to Buffalo.
                  



                    The total consideration including deferred consideration payments (cash and Shares) are based on the following milestones:
                  






                          Milestones
                        





                          Milestones (USD)
                        



                          USD Cash payments to Business
                        





                          Issue of Shares
                        



                          License and resale agreement
                        





                          All milestones as indicated below
                        



                          Per the schedule below
                        





                          None
                        





                          Settlement
                        



                          Accumulated cash payments by xTV to the Business
                        





                          US$13.5 million
                        





