                Conditions Precedent to the Proposed Acquisition
              




          As a result of the Proposed Acquisition, ASX may exercise its discretion to require the Company to obtain shareholder approval under ASX Listing Rule 11.1.2 for a significant change to the scale of the Company's activities or to re-comply with ASX's admission requirements. The Company is in discussions with ASX to determine the application of Chapter 11.
        




          Capital Raising
        



          In the event that the Option is exercised, and subject to shareholders' approval, xTV intends to undertake a capital raising to raise an indicative minimum amount of
        

          $10,000,000 on terms to be confirmed. The funds raised from the capital raising will be used for payment of consideration for the Proposed Acquisition and for additional working capital to support Company growth activities.
        





          INDICATIVE TIMETABLE
        




      An indicative timetable and other relevant information will be released to ASX, if and when the Option to acquire the Business is exercised.
    



      About xTV - Cloud TV Networks
    

      Allowing businesses to create dedicated multi-channel online networks that integrate branded video and user- generated content with other real-time feeds.
    

www.xtv.net www.xtv.tv




      For further information please contact
    




            Joe Ward CEO
          

            Joe.ward@xtv.net
          



            Jane Morgan
          

            Investor & Media Relations investors@xtv.net
          




